org.timepedia.chronoscope.client.render
Class ZoomInterval

java.lang.Object
  org.timepedia.chronoscope.client.render.ZoomInterval
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Comparable<ZoomInterval>
public class ZoomInterval
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<ZoomInterval>

Represents one of the zoom intervals (1d, 1m, 1y, 10y, etc.) that appear in the legend axis.

The natural ordering of ZoomInterval objects is ascending order based first on their intervals, and second on their names.

Author:
chad takahashi <chad@timepedia.org>

isFilterExempt

public boolean isFilterExempt()
True only if this zoom link should never be filtered, even if its interval falls outside of some external filtering criteria (e.g. the "max" zoom link should always be available to the user).

filterExempt

public ZoomInterval filterExempt(boolean isFilterExempt)
Intended to be called "method chaining" style. E.g. ZoomInterval myZoom = new ZoomInterval("foo", 10000).filterExempt(true).
